 on a course in as few strokes as possible. Major championships include the Masters, US Open, The Open Championship, and PGA Championship.", "Volleyball is a team sport where two teams of six players separate by a net try to score points by grounding the ball on the opponent's side. Indoor volleyball and beach volleyball are both Olympic sports with distinct rules."], "scores": [0.7560196158975769, 0.6717672751611296, 0.6469287898289997, 0.6358297669688929, 0.6299070124613526], "model_name": "bge-base", "document_ids": ["Soccer", "Rugby", "Baseball", "Golf", "Volleyball"]}}